{"word":"H1856 - דָּקַר - dâqar - daw-kar' - Pierce","slug":"H1856","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דָּקַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dâqar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>daw-kar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Pierce"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05E7;&#x05E8; - da&#x0302;qar</b> - <i>daw-kar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>stab</i>; by analogy to <i>starve</i>; figuratively to <i>revile: - </i>pierce, strike (thrust) through, wound."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1857\">H1857</a>, <a href=\"#/H4094\">H4094</a>"}]}